   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">How to deploy the Power Invoice Automation for Salesforce Quote to Cash Power Composer Starter Pack.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">What Quick Starts are Available?</b>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Quick Starts include all of the components needed for a document generation solution. The purpose of a Quick Start is to help you get up-and-running quickly with a pre-configured template and pre-determined data sources.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The QuickStart solutions for Power Invoice Generation for Salesforce Billing include:</p>
         <ul id="ul_llv_g3c_5cc" class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Account Statement</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Create Receipt</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Create Credit Memo</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Create Debit Memo</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Generate Invoice</li>
         </ul>
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">How Do You Deploy a QuickStart?</b>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">To deploy a Quick Start, follow these steps:</p>
      </context>
      <steps id="steps_vzm_fsc_5cc" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">When installing Power Invoice Generation, select Install for All Users.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select Power Invoice Generation from the App dropdown.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click the Power Quick Start tab.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the Quick Start you want to use.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click Go to Page Layouts.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Add the newly created Power Invoice Generation button to the Page layout and click
               Save.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
      <postreq class="- topic/section task/postreq ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">You will be prompted to enable Remote Sites when you select the QuickStart. You must do this in order for Power Invoice Generation to be able to create the button. Also, you must configure Configure Composer as a Connected App before using the solution.</p>
      </postreq>
